<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="comfortable-adj">comfortable <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'kʌmftəbl/    美 /'kʌmftəbl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>令人舒适的；舒适的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 uncomfortable </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a comfortable bed / hotel</strong>
舒适的床/宾馆</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(人) 舒服的；自在的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 uncomfortable </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please <strong>make yourself comfortable</strong>.
请别客气。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Leaning back, she put her feet onto the sofa to get comfortable.
为了舒服，她向后靠了靠，把脚放在沙发上。</p><footer>2011 江西</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>宽裕的；小康的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My parents are not wealthy but they’re quite comfortable. 
我的父母虽不富有，但他们生活还算宽裕。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>comfortably /'kʌmftəbli;'kʌmfətəbli/ adv   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>All the rooms were comfortably furnished.
所有的房间都配有舒适的家具。</p></div></div>